The paper focuses on instance-level Sketch-Based Image Retrieval (SBIR) tasks, which involves using deep learning techniques to recognize and retrieve images based on sketches. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of triplet loss and classification loss for optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of datasets and image processing techniques, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
